poly_attn: PE (Orange partner) and I have known each other longer and actually dated on and off for about 4 years, but we were extremely toxic together as a couple. I knew that if I were to stay with him long-term, it would come at the expense of my happiness, stability, and peace of mind. However, when we weren't in a committed, monogamous relationship with each other, we actually got along great, and are both still extremely attracted to each other, and enjoy many of the same things in bed and love to experiment together. I met DA (Blue partner) about 2 years after PE and I decided we could never be in a serious, long-term relationship. DA was everything PE wasn't - he made me feel safe, loved, and comfortable, and he's kind, reliable, committed, hardworking, generous, and loyal. When DA and I first got together, I initially cut PE off and didn't tell DA about my past with PE right away, as I thought it would become irrelevant. But then I realized that even though I could picture a comfortable, secure future with DA, I was realizing I would probably never feel the excitement, fun, and sexual attraction that PE and I had together. However, i still very much wanted a future with DA, I just hoped I wouldn't have to give up some of the things i enjoy and get excited about the most to do so, so I told DA about my history with PE and asked how he would feel about PE and I having a strictly sexual, non-emotional "relationship" while still being committed and emotionally invested in DA. He wasn't thrilled at first, but he did agree to it. Over the years though, I feel the dynamic has changed quite a bit from having one serious, steady, reliable and committed partner, and one "on the side" for fun, excitement, and amazing sexual chemistry, into a polyamorous situation where I consider them both to be my partners, and they both view it the same way too. They even talk sometimes and get along pretty well now. However, I fel that DA will always be slightly more important to me, and I consider us more committed to each other than PE and I are. I hope I would never be forced to choose between the 2 of them, but if I had to, I would definitely choose DA. Also, of course they both have the option of sleeping with other women too, which PE does on a semi-weekly basis, but as far as I know DA hasn't been with anyone but me since we got together. I think that factors into my decisions too, because I feel more valued and special to DA than I do to PE.
